Why are treatments called “1/2” instead of “Int/Ext”??
I suggest that anything that is NOT a number (=continous variables) should be given a name (with letters).

raw$manejo <- factor(raw$manejo, labels=c("Int", "Ext"))
table(raw$manejo)
